# E2E: Validation workflow

Any change to e2e or upgrade tests must be validated against **both** a BYOIDC cluster and a non-BYOIDC cluster before the fix is considered complete.

---

## Prerequisites

### 1. Know your target
- Which branch is being fixed (e.g. `main`, `v0.36.0-test-fix`)
- Which RHOAI version the image tag maps to (e.g. `3.5`)
- Whether the cluster under test is BYOIDC or non-BYOIDC

### 2. Credentials file (must be outside the repo — never commit it)
Store credentials at a path like `../creds` (one level above the repo root):

```
BYOIDC_ADMIN_USERNAME=<username>
BYOIDC_ADMIN_PASSWORD=<password>
BYOIDC_TEST_USERNAME=<username>
BYOIDC_TEST_PASSWORD=<password>
OCP_ADMIN_USER_USERNAME=<username>
OCP_ADMIN_USER_PASSWORD=<password>
TEST_USER_USERNAME=<username>
TEST_USER_PASSWORD=<password>
```

`OCP_API_URL` does **not** need to be in this file — `run-tests.sh` always infers it from the mounted kubeconfig (first tries `oc whoami --show-server`; falls back to `oc config view … .clusters[0].cluster.server`, which is always present).

The same credentials file works for both cluster types — `run-tests.sh` automatically promotes `BYOIDC_*` variables when a BYOIDC cluster is detected.

### 3. Active oc session
Log in to the target cluster before running:
```bash
oc whoami   # confirm you are on the correct cluster
```
On BYOIDC clusters, `oc whoami` works but `oc whoami --show-token=true` does not — that is intentional; the tests handle it via `get_oidc_tokens()`.

### 4. Ensure results directory exists
```bash
mkdir -p results
```

---

## Build the test image

```bash
# Build locally with the correct tag (no-cache prevents stale layers)
make build-test-image E2E_TEST_IMAGE_VERSION=<tag>   # e.g. 3.5
# Verify it exists before running tests
podman images | grep codeflare-sdk-tests
```

---

## Run tests — canonical podman run command

`--pull="never"` is mandatory when testing a locally built image.

```bash
podman run --rm -it --platform linux/amd64 --pull="never" \
  -v ~/.kube/config:/codeflare-sdk/tests/.kube/config:ro \
  -v ./results:/codeflare-sdk/tests/results:Z \
  --env-file ../creds \
  quay.io/opendatahub/codeflare-sdk-tests:<tag> -m <tier>
```

Replace `<tag>` with the image tag (e.g. `3.5`) and `<tier>` with one of the values below.

---

## Tier order and markers

Run in this order — `pre_upgrade` must pass before `post_upgrade` is meaningful:

| Order | Marker | Description |
|-------|--------|-------------|
| 1 | `smoke` | Quick sanity checks |
| 2 | `tier1` | Standard full suite |
| 3 | `pre_upgrade` | Creates state for upgrade test |
| 4 | `post_upgrade` | Validates state after upgrade |

---

## Cluster switching

To test both cluster types, `oc login` to each cluster in turn and re-run the same image:

```bash
oc login <byoidc-api-url> ...    # switch to BYOIDC cluster
# run all 4 tiers

oc login <standard-api-url> ...  # switch to non-BYOIDC cluster
# run all 4 tiers
```

The kubeconfig is mounted read-only so changes on the host take effect immediately for the next container run.

---

## Definition of done

A fix is complete only when **all 4 tiers pass on both BYOIDC and non-BYOIDC clusters**. A partial result (e.g. BYOIDC passing, non-BYOIDC failing) is not acceptable.
